# Styling Guide

The application uses Tailwind CSS with custom configuration:

- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) defines:
  - Custom color schemes
  - Dark mode configuration
  - Font family settings
  - Chat-specific colors

- Utility function [cn](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts) combines Tailwind classes using:
  - clsx for conditional class names
  - tailwind-merge for proper class merging

- Global styles are defined in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)

Best practices:
- Use the `cn` utility for class name composition
- Follow the defined color scheme for consistency
- Maintain dark mode compatibility
